Major Shrines Dedicated to Benzaiten * {{ill|Enoshima Shrine|en|Enoshima Shrine|qid=Q11259219|lt=Enoshima Shrine|1=Enoshima Shrine}} (Fujisawa City, Kanagawa Prefecture, Enoshima, one of Japan's Three Great Benzaiten Shrines) * {{ill|Zeniarai Benzaiten Ugafuku Shrine|en|Zeniarai Benzaiten Ugafuku Shrine|qid=Q642681|lt=Zeniarai Benzaiten Ugafuku Shrine|1=Zeniarai Benzaiten Ugafuku Shrine}} (Kamakura City, Kanagawa Prefecture) * Shimizu Benzaiten Shrine (Saku City, Nagano Prefecture) * {{ill|Tenkawa Daibenzaiten Shrine|ja|天河大弁財天社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenkawa Daibenzaiten Shrine|qq=}} (Tenkawa Village, Yoshino District, Nara Prefecture, one of Japan's Three Great Benzaiten Shrines){{efn2|The Benzaiten Shrine in Tenkawa Village is not normally open to the public and can only be viewed during the once-in-60-years grand unveiling (''gokaichō''). During this time, major events such as Noh performances and the ''Reitaisai'' (Grand Festival) are held, attracting tourists and worshippers from across the country to Tenkawa Village. Tenkawa Daibenzaiten Shrine is particularly popular among performing artists, with many prominent figures visiting from Tokyo and other regions. The most recent unveiling was on July 18, 2008.|qq=}} * {{ill|Koganeyama Shrine (disambiguation)|lt=Koganeyama Shrine (disambiguation)|lt=Koganeyama Shrine|ja|黄金山神社 (石巻市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koganeyama Shrine|qq=}} (Ishinomaki City, Miyagi Prefecture, Kinkasan) * {{ill|Rokkō Hime Daizen Shrine|ja|六甲比命神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokkō Hime Daizen Shrine|qq=}} (Nada Ward, Kobe City, Hyōgo Prefecture, Rokkosan Town) – A theory suggests that Benzaiten = {{ill|Seoritsuhime|ja|瀬織津姫|1=Seoritsu-hime|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seoritsuhime|13=User:Immanuelle/Seoritsu-hime|qq=}}, whose mausoleum is believed to be here. * {{ill|Benzaiten Shrine|ja|弁財天宮|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Benzaiten Shrine|qq=}} For shrines dedicated to Ichikishima-hime no Mikoto, refer to the {{ill|Munakata Three Goddesses|ja|宗像三女神|1=Three Munakata Goddesses|1=Three Munakata Goddesses|qq=Three Munakata Goddesses|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Munakata Three Goddesses|13=User:Immanuelle/Three Munakata Goddesses|qq=}} or {{ill|Ichikishima Shrines|lt=Ichikishima Shrines|lt=Ichikishima Shrine|ja|市杵島神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikishima Shrine|qq=}}. ==References == {{Munakata Faith|qq=}}
